Always a good time. Drinks aren't pricey. Security is usually nice. Tuesdays are fun electronic nights and weekends tend to be hip hop.
Parking is cheap or street parking is free. The crowds are usually really nice people,  especially on the Tuesday nights. Always a good option to get away from the weekly meta of work life<//review>

<Review>BEWARE - Do NOT purchase from this location.
BEWARE of ‚Äúmanager‚Äù JASON.

I purchased my vehicle in 2019 where the Tesla salesman stated that I would be receiving a $250 gift card and 1 year of valet as a rewards promo for purchasing at this specific location.

I followed up on my rewards upon delivery of my vehicle and the salesman reassured me that my info was sent off to the rewards department. I continued to follow up months after delivery, as I never heard back. The salesman started to ignore my messages and became less responsive after I took delivery of my vehicle. I have emails dated from 2019 through Jun 2020 regarding the follow up of my rewards. Even more disturbing is that I was told there were a whole bunch of people who had purchased their vehicle before me and still had not received their rewards.

After a full year has passed and being patient for this reward, I decided to call Tesla on Dec 2020 where I was redirected to the manager, JASON. He sent an email to the rewards department and I did not get a reply for 4 weeks; I finally got a reply at the end of Jan 2021. The rewards department stated that Tesla never sent my information to them so that I was no longer eligible for the rewards, as the program expired on Sep 2020. Even though I explained that I purchased my vehicle in 2019, they said they could not do anything for me. Jason remained silent and did not reply at all, even though I sent him an email expressing concern over the lack of organization and responsiveness from him and his team. The disorganization is clear between Tesla and the rewards company, where they will not take accountability for screwing over customers.

Take your money elsewhere. This location will scam you into buying a vehicle from their specific location and then they will ignore you after they take your money.< /Review><rate>1< /rate>< name>

<Date>1593019481958</Date><Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
Test drive vehicles are parked on the 7th floor and you drive cars contactless now due to covid. They give you a little run down of how you'll get to the car and they'll unlock for you. Might be a good idea to get a little info on the car and how to use it and the features before your test drive.

The showroom is clean and they, at least now, have the cars you'll want to test drive. Even a model Y.

Nice people and a fun location for shopping! The test drive area is a little busy but you can take the car past that area and get to one with more space or a Highway.

I definitely recommend this location if you're in the area.< /review>

< review>
Several of my friends have been visiting this place quite a bit as they have all bought their cars from this location. It's a pretty neat place to visit if you want to check out the different Tesla cars. They have the Models 3, S, and X cars on display.

Along the walls, they have interactive TV displays that presents information about their products and features. From home charging and Autopilot to their Power Wall exhibits, you'll definitely be able to learn a little something here.

During the last few times we visited, the staff that helped us out were pretty nice. They listened to our questions and concerns while providing answers that satisfied our curiosity. However, there were also times when we tried to call in and were directed to voice mailboxes that were full; couldn't leave a message even if we wanted to!

Overall, it's a neat place to learn more about Tesla products. And if you want to buy a car, the reps would gladly help you walk through the process on their computers. You could also request a test drive there. Don't forget about the 7th floor of the parking structure: Supercharging stations!< /review>

<userid>105014884086626784884</userid><name>Alex Nunez</name>< Time>

<rate>5<//rate>< Text>
Tesla, you had me at $100.

This review is going to be fun for me. I have a lot to say, but my goal is to be as helpful as possible and not babble on. I will try to be concise.

It's been about eight years since I've had a new car and I usually get a reliable used car. I like putting my money toward investments and not expensive vehicles. Tesla Model 3 had too much value to pass up this time around.

I will first discuss my buying experience, things I've learned, and any tips that may be helpful.

TEST DRIVE -  I called Tesla at the Americana and scheduled a test drive. It's important to be on-time for your appointments as they are known to get pretty booked up. I ended up being 20 minutes late, but they still fit me in right away, which was great. I made sure to test drive the Model 3 Standard Plus as this was the price range I wanted. I know myself if I test drove the performance model, I'd be hooked and scraping money together to get it. Driving a Tesla for the first time was a bit surreal, but I did feel an itch to floor-it but held back as my Tesla driving instructor was monitoring me. Overall that car was the best vehicle I've ever driven in terms of speed, handling, and feel. So now what?

BUYING - I sat down with Luis, my Tesla Owner Advisor. He answered my question, which was basically about the pricing and delivery of my Tesla and gave me no pressure to buy. He helped me log in to my account that I had already created to reserve the test drive. For $100, I started my order for a Tesla, which is ludicrous. Getting full self-driving for the extra 7k charge with your Tesla is a given at this point, I mean come on. Estimated was about 30-45 days for my car to be ready which varys for everyone.

PRO TIP - While you're waiting for delivery, you should take this time to learn about charging your Tesla and possibly get an electrician out to your home. Yelp helped me search for an electrician to help me install either a Nema 14-50 or Tesla wall charger. What I discovered at the 4-plex I'm renting at is that the electrical wiring for the property would need a complete overhaul before being able to add any new outlets. Thankfully my insurance office in San Fernando has a plug right outside, so no issue there.

DELIVERY - After a month of checking my status in my Tesla account, I received a text message prompting me to set up an appointment and complete my payment online before taking delivery. I had already uploaded my insurance, finished my Tesla financing option at 3.19%. I ran into one issue when I had accidentally backed out of my pre-approved financing at 3.19% to see the other payment options. It was like my pre-approval disappeared, and the system wanted me to go in and re-submit. I did not want the system to ding me for another credit inquiry, and I know that usually, a pre-approval is good for at least 30 days. I was able to call up Luis at Tesla, and he was able to see my pre-approval on his end and get it to pop back up for me, which was a relief.

TESLA INSURANCE: I quoted insurance with Tesla, but it was still more expensive than my current insurance office Farmers Insurance Alex Nunez in San Fernando :). I have an Umbrella, Renters, Car, and Life Insurance altogether, and it's just cheaper with all the combined discounts, and I like my limits over a million.

PICK UP - I arrived at Tesla in Burbank and was invited to sit in on a brief Tesla introduction presentation. Everyone at Tesla had a smile on their face, and customer service was excellent. At the close, they get you logged into your Tesla app and have you honk your hour and find your car. It was enjoyable and just a great experience overall.

DRIVING - So far, it's been fantastic. I've been able to enjoy autopilot and enjoy the speed, and boy does it accelerate! I've been charging at home getting 6/miles an hour of charge on a standard 120V outlet, which has been ok for my daily commute.

If you found this review helpful, please smash the "LIKE" button on this review as this helps with the Google algorithm, and I'd REALLY appreciate it :)</Text>

< Text>
From the outside the advertising is great. The interior was clean and orderly. The menu looks great. Then comes time for execution. I ordered a chicken sandwich with ranch and  tots. The chicken was thin and the edges were like leather. Tots were enough for 3-4 people. Not sure if the owner cares about profitability or not. Last thing, the mango madness sauce tastes like Tabasco mixed with bbq and a touch of vinegar, tastes nothing like mango, disgusting. The beer selection on tap is the same as any other place that serves beer on tap, nothing special. There is a lot of chicken sandwich competition, wicked falls way short of being a competitor. Fix the kitchen and your business will grow, or replace management with people that know what they are doing.

*** added comment. $8.57 for modelo draft!! Seriously over priced.

Update: thanks for the math lesson. 3-2=1</Text>

We came here for lunch using a Living Social coupon at $15 for $30. I use coupons because I work too hard for my money and appreciate a savings.  This place was a pizza place before and looks like it was completely redone and too the better.

We place our order at the counter and one item the people there could not figure out the discount.  I ordered a chicken sandwich, which came with fries and a drink, my wife ordered the wrap, same thing (fries and drink) and my son the tenders.

The flavor was pretty good and I enjoyed it, the sandwich had some tender chicken and the fries were seasoned.   My wife finished only half the wrap and took the rest home, but she enjoyed the flavors and the chicken and had nothing bad to say about it.  My son's tenders had a sauce that gave it a color that was less than attractive (more brown than red) you figure out what he was calling it...rhymed with herd.

He said the flavor was okay but would opt for a different sauce since they have around six to choose from.  The people were friendly and let me take tons of photos which I am sharing.  I would say it was a decent lunch.</Text>

We had a really great experience with Paddle Sports. The staff was very nice and got us onto the water quickly. We did a walk-in kayak rental and had zero issues. < Text>
This is one of my favorite places to eat in the South Bay.  They have a few  other locations but I have been to this one the most.  I like that its kind of cozy so it isn't too big so large groups over 8 would be tough. Parking lot is a bit small but there is a Post Office parking lot you can use after hours. Their menu is full of normal Mexican fare and there are combinations. They also have a kids menu they hand out with crayons. Personally my go tos are, I love the soup (Xolchi, pronounced sol-chee) It has chicken rice and avocados, it is hearty and healthy especially if you're feeling under the weather.  My other favorite are all the burritos are great, one of my favorites is the Asher (it has egg, chicken & Avocado).  They have great fresh chips and salsa too.  The staff is always amazing and helpful.  My kids loves it too.</Text>

<user_name>Neat Gifts< /user_name><user>101297368107860883732< /user>< gmap_id>
0x80c2b38b224e8727:0x307f45aca6b6c9</gmap_id>
<Review>I kind of hate giving a negative review on a business when the staff are so friendly and helpful, but I went to this restaurant because Google maps recommended it and from the photos on Google maps, I thought the food looked tasty.

If you have ever been to England or heard about the lack of seasoning in their food, you might begin to understand why I was so disappointed with El Gringo Manhattan. Actually, the difference between this place and food in England is that every item the three of us has at El Gringo was so very salty, when in England there isn't much salt or any other seasoning in their food.

The other problem my family and I had was the lack of taste besides salt and a hint of metallic flavor in each item.

So, I had a one item combination meal for $11, a chili relano for $5 and a Shirley Temple that cost a whopping $3.75. That drink taste like a weak Sprite. My 12 soda lover wouldn't drink the entire soda. My wife had an alacart enchilada that cost $4 and my daughter had a barrito with a salad off the kids menu. All of that equaled just over $28.

That was a one timer for all of us.
If you like salty American style Mexican food, then you will probably enjoy El Gringo Manhattan. If you only like the real thing and not seasoned with a truck load of salt like me and my family, then I wouldn't recommend this place.</Review><response>None<//response><Pics>None</Pics></record>
</dataset><record>

< text>
We can't get enough of Takao's delicious Specials!  The menu is consistently fresh and well prepared.  The team seems to be entirely Japanese and as a result the high level of workmanship is clearly evident in the various dishes presented on the menu.  There is a low key atmosphere and simple design approach at play here compare to high end Japanese  establishments in Brentwood.  Yet what matters most, Foods and customer service are always on point.  Highly recommend this wonderful neighborhood Sushi Bar.<//text>

<GmapID>0x80c2bca0082154db:0xb4f70fa5ab19be44</GmapID>< Text>
I found out about the place because of Netflix documentary Chef's Table and since then always wanted to go and meet Chef Takao and taste his food. I finally got to go and ordered the Omakase menu. It was a whole new and different experience and I got to taste really different Japanese dishes from what I'm used to in my country and my trips abroad. It was quite an interesting experience overall and I even got to take a picture with Takao! He's a very nice and humble person. Service is very good, starting from the moment you book your reservation. The restaurant has kind of a family vibe and they make you feel very welcomed. That's probably why a lot of locals visit the place and are regular customers. I stayed for a while talking to one of those customers and got the chance to speak a little bit with Takao and his crew. It's definitely a place you want to visit if you have the chance. Enjoy!<//Text>

<Time>1368892194708<//Time>< user_id>
107733517992481483697<//user_id>
< text>
We ate lite so didn't venture far into the menu; that didn't keep us from admiring the BEAUTIFUL things distributed to fellow diners over the night or overhearing pleased diners who enthused openly (sometimes loudly) over something delicious. When I entered most of the tables had reserved signs. They were filled from that point on in the evening.

The sushi we did get was quiet and delicious. Texture is sometimes the most important thing in raw foods. You don't notice it so much unless it's bad, or really good. It's really good at Takao. Their little rolls looked beautiful. Things resting on banana leaves, cooked items, looked delicious.

The decor is clean, simple and light. It's much more lovely than it appears from outside. It's a little tight, especially at the sushi bar where we sat.

Overall, very nice.</text>

<GmapID>0x80c2bca0082154db:0xb4f70fa5ab19be44<//GmapID>< text>
Takao still provides an exceptional culinary experience. The cuts of his fish carried the day, with the wait staff providing immediate and courteous service. Kudos to the team.

This review is not five stars because it seemed as if the portions were smaller in quantity and variety than my two previous visits (noted on Yelp). I believe they are making an effort to remain at the prices I recall from my 2014 visit, although, again, price is not a real issue when visiting Takao.

I will return, so it's not like I'm upset. :)< /text>

Delicious food across the board from sashimi to Japanese egg custard. Very fresh and the crispy rice  with toro and caviar is heavenly. Food is 6 - 7 stars. Sadly, though usually the service is prompt and courteous, on this occasion the service was extremely poor - 0 stars and was a real detraction from the meal. Usually when there is a problem with service, restaurants attempt to rectify this during the course of the meal; unfortunately on this occasion this was not the case.<//Review>

< text>
I have only been once, but I had the most delicious gnocchi ever. I had it with the pesto cream, but you can also do a pink sauce if you prefer. They were perfect little pillows, light and smooth. All too often they're dense and chewy, but this was not the case. The pesto cream sauce had a lot of flavor and seemed home-made. It was the perfect portion to fill up, but not feel like I ate too much for lunch. I still had just enough room for a yummy piece of tiramisu. Glad I went to this little gem. Hope to make it back over there again sometime soon!</text>

< text>
Very nice park to visit in the summer!  A lot of big trees making it mostly shade here. The playground is a newer one for the kids to play on. There are little bbqs avaliable next to the picnic tables for when u have any get together or parties. Plenty of room for jump houses and running around. A great park for birthday parties. The restrooms here used to be open but recently have been welded shut for unknown reason.<//text>

<user_name>Arno Clair</user_name><date>1603300255558</date><rate>5< /rate>< Review>
Without a doubt the most knowledgeable plumbers out there.  That said, their "pricing" is wonky.  I've been using them for 15 years at two different houses.  It's always a haggle.  The on scene guy gives you a price range, but the manager by phone makes the final adjustments when you start breaking down the per item/service price.  Once you get past all that though, you'd be hard pressed to find a better crew with more resources available to you...one job I had 3 van loads of guys at my house.  So you DO get what you pay for.  It's a love/hate relationship.  I wouldn't want anyone else working on my house....but it's always a bit of a tussle at the beginning.  If you're comfortable asking questions and putting in some work, these guys won't disappoint.</Review>

<Text>I had a simple leaking faucet like most people do so I called Dutton Plumbing in Santa Clarita. When the service tech arrived, I explained the problem and symptoms of the leak and showed him that when I applied light downward pressure to the hot water handle, the drip would stop. This guy, without ever looking under the sink or taking the water handle off to inspect the fixture told me that my entire faucet fixture would have to be rebuilt and replace the shut off valves under the sink or only replace the valves. Without inspecting the valves or the faucet itself, he gave a quote for $515 for replacing the valves and $795 for rebuilding the faucet and replacing the valves, both of which I declined as the cost seemed unusually high.

I emailed the company that manufactured the faucet and provided the exact same description of the problem via email that I gave Dutton Plumbing‚Äôs service tech in person. The faucet manufacturer replied back suggesting that I replace the seats and springs under the faucet handle and provided me with the part number. I purchased a two pack of the part for $4.98 and a tube of silicone grease for $4.00 at Home Depot and installed them myself in 10 minutes, resulting in the leak being fixed.

Dutton Plumbing not only misdiagnosed how to fix the leak, they suggested work that did not EVEN need to be done at the cost of nearly $800. They do this stuff for a living, so how could they not EVEN suggest replacing the seats and springs? But instead, he told me that I need to replace my entire faucet fixture and valve handles. I don't like being cheated and that is exactly what this place tried to do to me.

DO NOT let them do any work until you get a second opinion and estimate. They wanted to charge me $800 for work that did not need to be done AT ALL and I ended up fixing the leak myself and it literally cost me LESS THAN the price of a movie ticket. Read the Yelp reviews and you'll see a pattern of them trying to overcharge people.

I spoke to someone at the Dutton after they saw my review and he tried to make up an excuse, saying that they might suggest repairs that are "more comprehensive." There's a big difference between "more comprehensive" and repairs that are not required AT ALL. Crooks!<//Text>< pictures>

<username>Laura C</username>< text>
We have used Dutton Plumbing for years and have been happy with them until this last guy!  We got a call about a free annual inspection of our water heater and toilets so we had the guy come out to take a look.  At first, he was nice and greeted me outside.
I showed him the water heater, which was in good shape, or so he said.

His disposition seemed to change once he got into the house.  He seemed to be judging us and our house because we are poor and on a fixed income and can not afford nice things. I saw the guy looking around and making faces at our stuff.  I didn't say anything because I thought it was going to end there and I was used to people judging our stuff, which isn't a big deal.

We had 2 of our 3 dogs in a training crate so they wouldn't jump on the guy and knock him down.  He used the word "cage" when he saw them and we corrected him.  I could tell he was judging us, even after we had already explained it to him we did not want them knocking him down and that we had just put them in the crate once we heard the knock on the door.  They are spoiled and well fed, so I had hoped he would have seen that and let it go at that.  He proceded to make rude comments and noises about our house and asked if something on the back of our sons' toilet was pee.  I said I did not know (because it was the toilet our autistic son uses and he sometimes might miss) and hoped he saw embarrassment and humiliation on my face from his comment.  By this point I thought he was just being rude and hostile.  I guess he didn't see the look on my face because he kept going.
The dogs were still barking from a stranger being in the house.  I just walked away from him, told him I was putting and put all the dogs outside so I could hear what he had to say.  I figured he was having a bad day, so I tried to let it go.  I just wanted this over at this point so he could leave.  He quoted us some astronomical price for fixing a running toilet in our bathroom, I thanked him and thought that was the end, but it wasn't.  I figured he just made up the high price because he didnt want to do the work, which was fine by me because I wanted him gone by that time.  I never made faces or said anything to him because I thought he was taking his bad day out on us, but I really felt humiliated and embarrassed.  I was so ready to let it go and move on with my life

It didnt end there though:  About an hour later, we get a knock on the door from Animal Control about how our dogs were in a "cage" all day long, which is not true, and that the lady had to see them and take a picture of them and write up a report!  We have never been so embarrassed and humiliated in all our lives.
We are NEVER using Dutton Plumbing again!  I AM LIVID THAT HE EMBARRASSED US LIKE THAT!  HE WAS UNPROFESSIONAL AND RUDE!  I was trying to let it go, but now I can't.

Never hire this company!  Never!  I could understand if our dogs were emaciated or mangy looking, which they weren't so I dont know why the guy called Animal Control on us!   Our dogs are well taken care of!  Smh!  I  Now, I wish I had said something and kicked him out for being so rude!  Now, there's a report about our dogs on file with Animal Control!  Thanks Dutton Plumbing! I don't know why they hire plumbers like that because he's not people friendly!  I'm calling Corporate on Monday.  I dont care if it is close to Christmas.</text>

Dutton staff are beyond professional - they are courteous and attentive, kind and polite. They treat you and your home with respect, using abundant covers to avoid tracking dirt and vacuums to minimize dust.  You get text  and images of the workers to ID who's coming to your house. <Gmap_id>0x80e82ebed5b30749:0x6a99858c7f6e0140< /Gmap_id>< text>
I had a simple clog that couldn't be resolved with a bladder or consumer-grade auger. Heard good things about these guys from a friend, so I called. My call was answered by someone who spoke english, and was able to confirm a time to call me back to set an exact appointment time (same day). I didn't get a call back initially, so I called and rescheduled for the following day as I could not wait at home any longer. After that, smooth sailing. The dispatcher called me that next morning confirming a time, and then the repair man called me when he got there. He was cool enough to wait a few minutes for my fiance to get there. It took him 25 minutes to fix the clog and he was on his way. The price remained consistent, no surprises. This would have been 5 stars if I had initially gotten a call back like i was promised. However that being said, I would absolutely use these guys again.< /text>

< review>
I highly recommend this company if you need an honest accurate estimate for any plumbing problem. Everyone at Dutton Plumbing was very professional and curious.  I called for an estimate regarding a possible slab leak. The technicians arrived on time as scheduled.  I was greeted at my door by Matt; who immediately placed a clean mat on my door step, put on clean cover shoes over his work shoes. Matt accessed my situation very quickly entered my options with the exact cost on his iPad (which was very reasonable compared to other quotes I received). I opted for the slab fix..the by-pass option would also have fixed the hot water pipe leak in the slab. Within a 30 minutes Matt had located the exact location of the leak, and identified the hot water pipe. He prepared the work area, carefully removed 4 titles (without breaking them) and started the work to open up the cement to access the pipe.  Matt found the copper pipe with the leak. He then very carefully silver soldered the new pipe in place, wrapped the pipe with a thick rubber jacket, back-filled the hole in the slab, poured in quick drying cement to seal the floor. Matt‚Äôs work was meticulous, neat and professional. I am one happy customer ..and would recommend you call Dutton Plumbing if you ever need a professional plumbing job. Thanks again Matt for your expertise it is much appreciated.  Tony</review>

<Rating>4<//Rating><review>I had a drainage leak beneath my kitchen sink.  I tried fixing it for three days myself but it would not stop leaking. Admitting defeat I called Dutton Plumbing. Normally I would have gotten three bids but after three days of fighting leaks that trashed my bottom cabinet shelf, I relented figuring if it was good enough for Mom, then go with it.  Steve explained the piping was the PVC pipe, gaskets and slip rings were old and best replaced entirely. After four hours of work, except for the Garbage Disposal, everything was replaced. <userid>110062763213439935022< /userid><user_name>Anna J< /user_name><date>1522103761534< /date><rate>5</rate>< Review>
Danny D and Leo B provided service for our residence on a leaking faucet and water pressure regulator. Danny was the main technician and Leo assisted him. Danny was very knowledgable, professional, courteous and friendly. He took time to explain the problem to us, how he planned to approach remedying it and the relative costs. As for expertise and professionalism, their service was excellent. I was especially pleased by Dan's positive professional demeanor. They were prompt, finished the work within the quoted timeframe, explained their process beforehand so we knew exactly what services we were receiving, and they left their workspace as clean as they found it. As for cost, we have worked with less expensive plumbers in the past, so Dutton is not the most competitive provider in terms of pricing, however with Dan's professionalism and a very organized business service model (we have not experienced a more organized effort, from front office to completion), customers can reasonably expect to pay a bit more than what a sole provider/owner-operator would charge that doesn't offer such a comprehensive service model, which includes your initial call, prompt scheduling, phone updates, e-mail updates and accurate time estimations for both technician arrival and work performance. We might have been able to shop around for a cheaper solution since this call was not an emergency call, but overall, we feel we have received value for our dollar.</Review>

To prevent these issues, Dutton Plumbing installed a pressure control regulator 3 or 4 years ago, but warned the hard water in the area would take its toll.  This year we had two more leaks.  We requested Luis Zamarripa as our annual service technician.  He is an excellent, dependable technician and he drives PINK DUTTON PLUMBING TRUCK.  10% of the profits from the PINK trucks go to the Susan G. Komen Foundation.
Luis recommended a whole house water filter to which we agreed.  He included the leak repair and did an excellent installation job.  We got an 18 month same as cash deal so it was very affordable.

We had Luis Zamarripa back on 9/12/18 to install a pre-purchased RO unit under our kitchen sink.  The installation concerned me because Luis Z. and Lon Ralston had to cut a new hole in the sink to mount the RO faucet.  The installation was perfect. No cracks in the sink, which is over 20 years old, and NO LEAKS under the sink.  I've been told that can be a common problem with RO installations.
Additionally, Luis and Lon, replaced our old dishwasher air gap.  We requested this extra work and asked for the air gap to match our upgraded sink faucet.  The match is a good one and the Luis and Lon's workmanship is excellent.

Called Dutton office at 7:00 AM, they said someone would be there between 9-11, no problem, then got call saying they would be there in 30 mins, they showed up almost 45 mins, again no problem.

The plumbing problem was a broken PVC pipe in the Meter box, easy to get to.  Well my Father was a plumber and I spent many years helping, so I know whats involved, this is a 15 minute, job 20 if you run into roots.  The guys showed up from Dutton in a nice new van, in pristine white shirts, carrying what looks like a doctors bag. I tried not to laugh out loud, wondering if they realized they were plumbers not doctors.  I told them they would not need all that its a simple pipe repair.   They then took about 10 mins to write up a estimate which was $816.00, but he was very proud that he was able to save me $134.00 and that's how he got it down to $816.00.  I told him he must be mistaken.  When he looked at me as if i was stupid I told him to take his fancy bag get back in his truck and get out of here.  That I am happy to pay a fair price but that was ridiculous and that I hope they don't rip everyone off in the same manner.

BTW Gordan Taylor Plumbing came out right away did the job in about 15 mins.  and I had him tend to a few other issues I had been meaning to fix like my R/O filter system under my sink, check my pressure regulator, test the pressure on the house, check a gas line to my fire pit. WOW I am sure when Dutton would add these other items I would have to take a loan out on the house to pay their bill.  BTW Gordon Taylor Plumbing did the whole job for under $200.00.

The odd thing is the guy from Dutton did not even seem surprised at my response I guess he hears it often.  I never got a call back trying to explain or appologize.  I realize companies are allowed to charge what they like, but at rates like that I am fearful for the people who don't know any better.  I had heard of a senior citizen who had them change a water heater for nearly $3,000.00 and I dismissed it as urban legend as that was just crazy pricing and who would pay such an amount, but now i must wonder if this was a myth.  I have been told their Plumbers work on a commissions.

I have used Dutton before and they were expensive, but this time they were crazy.  They have lost my business and have earned a special place as I will tell everyone of my experiences.  I wonder how many people they actually take advantage of like this.<//Text>
